&lt;p&gt;The East Kent Neuropsychiatry Service is a multidisciplinary team (Neuropsychiatrist, Nursing, and Psychology) providing outpatient therapy to adults presenting mainly with Functional Neurological Disorders (e.g. dissociative non-epileptic seizures) and also to adults presenting with comorbid psychiatric and neurological conditions (e.g. multiple sclerosis).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an interesting post with opportunities to provide individual and group therapies to this diverse patient group and the post holder is expected to closely liaise and collaborate with multidisciplinary team colleagues. You will be supervised by the Principal Clinical Psychologist (0.6 wte) from the East Kent Neuropsychiatry Service and there additional are opportunities to carry out neuropsychological assessments and to develop skills in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relationships within the wider neuropsychology service are supportive, and there is a peer supervision network. There are also links with the Salomons Clinical Psychology Training Scheme and opportunities to carry out research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please call Dr Rachel Dean, Principal Clinical Psychologist. Tel: 07557 604 979.&lt;/p&gt;
